  .row
    .col-lg-6
      .card.mb-4
        .card-header
          |  Additional content
        .card-body
          p
            | Alert can also incorporate supplementary HTML elements like heading, paragraph, and divider.
          +example()
            .alert.alert-success(role='alert')
              h4.alert-heading Well done!
              p
                | Aww yeah, you successfully read this important alert message. This example text is going to run a bit longer so that you can see how spacing within an alert works with this kind of content.
              hr
              p.mb-0
                | Whenever you need to, be sure to use margin utilities to keep things nice and tidy.
    // /.col
    .col-lg-6
      .card.mb-4
        .card-header
          |  Dismissing
        .card-body
          p Using the JavaScript plugin, it’s possible to remove any alert.
          ul
            li Be sure you’ve loaded the bootstrap alert plugin or the compiled CoreUI JavaScript.
            li
              | Add a close button and the
              code  .alert-dismissible
              |  class, which adds some extra padding to the right of the alert component and positions the
              code  .close
              |  button.
            li
              | On the close button, add the
              code  data-coreui-dismiss="alert"
              |  attribute, which triggers the JavaScript functionality. You have to use the
              code  &lt;button&gt;
              |  element with it for proper behavior across all devices.
            li
              | To animate alerts when dismissing them, you have to add the
              code .fade
              |  and
              code .show
              |  classes.
          p You can see this in action with a live demo:
          +example()
            .alert.alert-warning.alert-dismissible.fade.show(role='alert')
              .fw-semibold Holy guacamole!
              |  You should check in on some of those fields below.
              button.btn-close(type='button', data-coreui-dismiss='alert', aria-label='Close')
  // /.row
